  "description": "Post-quantum document signing and on-chain attestation. Signs arbitrary payloads with ML-DSA-65 (NIST FIPS 204), producing a self-contained JSON envelope any counterparty can verify. Optionally anchors the envelope hash on Armature L1 for a permanent timestamped on-chain record.",
